social_posts.post_text: We just checked the numbers and can't believe it- In 2022, we adopted out 546 surrendered reptiles and amphibians through our Adoption Island rescue program! 😍
Roger is looking rather snazzy today 🤩
Happy Valentine's Day from Cheyenne!
Possibly the cutest baby to hatch here at Snake Discovery 😍
Rex's last feeding was pretty exciting, especially for the kids in her dome!
Sharon the apple destroyer (This is a very rare treat for her, but she LOVES apples!)
I just want to read my book 😭😂 Apparently Cheyenne needs attention...

Rattlesnakes often use "rectilinear locomotion" to move forward! It works like this: Imagine their rib bones moving like a millipede's many legs. Now imagine a scaly 'sock' covering everything. And there you have a snake.
Goofy girl made her own hoodie! (Madagascar Giant Hognose Snakes)
He came face to face with Rex 😂
Taco the softshell turtle is totally hidden. "If I can't see you, you can't see me."

Thank you again @visioncagesracks for your incredibly generous donation of Vision Cages plus custom-fitting cage liners to Adoption Island! We use these cages daily for the 500+ animals that get surrendered/adopted annually. Thanks for helping us find homes for reptiles in need! 
We use the cage liners for bearded dragons, leopard geckos, and other arid species. They fit great and make cleanup so easy!
Serenity loves attention from those he bonds with. He's available for adoption at Snake Discovery!
